-- Ontario Teachers' Not Anxious to Sell Majority Stake in Maple Leaf Sports
-- B y   H u g o   M i l l e r
-- 2010-12-03T20:56:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/ontario-teachers-not-anxious-to-sell-majority-stake-in-maple-leaf-sports.html
The Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan
said it has never received an offer for the company that owns
the Toronto Maple Leafs hockey team and the Raptors basketball
club and is not keen to sell it.  “We are not now, nor have we ever been anxious to sell our
investment in” Maple Leaf Sports & Entertainment Ltd., Chief
Executive Officer Jim Leech said in an e-mailed statement today.
He added that the pension fund manager is not now in
negotiations to sell its majority stake in the company.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
